    "repo-mindmap-workflow": {
      "roomId": "repo-mindmap-workflow",
      "topic": "Repository Mindmap Workflow",
      "createdAt": "2026-06-04T20:02:32.228Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-06-04T20:02:32.228Z",
      "state": "Created",
      "notePath": "rooms/room-repo-mindmap-workflow/notes.txt",
      "artifactPath": "rooms/room-repo-mindmap-workflow/artifact.md",
      "noteText": "Summary\nThe project supports generating a subject from a repository, refreshing it in-app, and exploring relationships as an architecture map.\n\nKey Points\n- The README lists a 3-step flow: generate, refresh/load, then traverse.\n- The flow is positioned for onboarding and architecture review sessions.\n- It emphasizes understanding module boundaries and runtime flow through graph traversal.\n\nRecall Question\nWhat are the three steps described for exploring a repository as a dungeon mindmap?",
